#. type: Title ===
#, no-wrap
msgid "Downloading, Building, and Deploying Application Code"
msgstr "アプリケーションコードのダウンロード、ビルドおよびデプロイ"

#. type: Plain text
msgid "The project and code for the application you are going to secure is available in link:{quickstartRepo_link}[{quickstartRepo_name}].  You will need the following installed on your machine and available in your PATH before you can continue:"
msgstr "セキュリティ保護をしようとしているアプリケーションのプロジェクトとコードは、link:{quickstartRepo_link}[{quickstartRepo_name}] で入手できます。続行する前に、マシンに下記をインストールして、\"PATH\"を通しておく必要があります。"

#. type: Plain text
msgid "Java JDK 8"
msgstr "Java JDK 8"

#. type: Plain text
msgid "Apache Maven 3.1.1 or higher"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
msgid "Git"
msgstr "Git"

#. type: Plain text
msgid "ifeval::[{project_community}==true] You can obtain the code by cloning the repository at {quickstartRepo_link}. The quickstarts are designed to work with the most recent Keycloak release.  endif::[]"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
msgid "ifeval::[{project_product}==true] You can obtain the code by cloning the repository at {quickstartRepo_link}. Use the branch matching the version of {project_name} in use.  endif::[]"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
msgid "Follow these steps to download the code, build it, and deploy it. Make sure your {appserver_name} application server is started before you run these steps."
msgstr "以下の手順に沿って、コードをダウンロード、ビルド、およびデプロイします。但し、以下の手順を実行する前に、必ず {appserver_name} アプリケーションサーバーが起動している状態にしておきます。"

#. type: Block title
#, no-wrap
msgid "Clone Project"
msgstr ""

#. type: delimited block -
#, no-wrap
msgid "$ git clone {quickstartRepo_link}\n"
"$ cd {quickstartRepo_dir}/app-profile-jee-vanilla\n"
"$ mvn clean wildfly:deploy\n"
msgstr "$ git clone {quickstartRepo_link}\n"
"$ cd {quickstartRepo_dir}/app-profile-jee-vanilla\n"
"$ mvn clean wildfly:deploy\n"

#. type: Plain text
msgid "You should see some text scroll down in the application server console window.  After the application is successfully deployed go to:"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
msgid "http://localhost:8080/vanilla"
msgstr "http://localhost:8080/vanilla"

#. type: Block title
#, no-wrap
msgid "Application Login Page"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
msgid "image:{project_images}/app-login-page.png[]"
msgstr "image:{project_images}/app-login-page.png[]"

#. type: Plain text
msgid "If you open up the application's _web.xml_ file you would see that the application is secured via `BASIC` authentication.  If you click on the login button on the login page, the browser will pop up a BASIC auth login dialog."
msgstr ""

#. type: Block title
#, no-wrap
msgid "Application Login Dialog"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
msgid "image:{project_images}/client-auth-required.png[]"
msgstr "image:{project_images}/client-auth-required.png[]"

#. type: Plain text
msgid "The application is not secured by any identity provider, so anything you enter in the dialog box will result in a `Forbidden` message being sent back by the server.  The next section describes how you can take this deployed application and secure it."
msgstr ""

